    "summary": "An Educational Designer & Researcher with experience in ICT in Education for more then thirty years in Higher Education in the Netherlands, Hungary and Ghana, especially in Teacher Training College and Primary School. Program Manager in the field of  integration of ICT in education, E-learning and Digitalisation of Knowledge. Change Manager in the field of Higher Education, building new educational concepts to improve the quality of teaching and learning.\n\nFrom 1992 until 2003: workshops and training at the Teacher Training College of the K\u00e1roli G\u00e1sp\u00e1r University in Nagyk\u00f6r\u00f6s, Hungary, on the subject of curriculum development of mathematics and ICT in primary school and in Teacher Training Education.\n\nWritten a research paper \u2018Educational Designing with MicroWorlds\u2019 that has been published in the Journal of Technology and Teacher Education, Volume 15, Issue 4, 2007. This research paper inform educators about the development and use of the module \u2018Computer Images for Lesson Support\u2019 for primary teacher education that aims at educating prospective teachers in designing multimedia-learning environments with the aid of the Logo program MicroWorlds and using it with children.\n\nFrom December 2006 until March 2007 written a Feasibility Study Report for the Ministry of Education, Sports & Science of Ghana for a project focused on the enhancement of the use of ICT in Education at 38 TTC\u2019s (Teacher Training Colleges) throughout Ghana. From April 2007 writing the educational concept and working on the realization of the Education Quality Improvement Program (EQIP) in Ghana.\n\nFrom 2007 active as Freelance Educational Designer & Researcher and Secretary & Program Director Education and ICT of the Change4Africa Foundation, a NGO in The Netherlands that has develop knowledge about the use of\u00a0ICT in Innovative Programs\u00a0to improve Education, Good Governance and Good Entrepreneurship in Ghana.\n\nFrom the beginning of 2013 professionalized the hobby of gastronomy and wine.\n\nSpecialties: Consultant in Educational Design & Research and ICT,  focussed on educational innovation and knowledge development for all levels of education.",
